## 📊 Final Audit: Log Analytics
To provide 100% certainty that the remediation worked, I inspected the Diagnostic Logs (`proj1_loganalytics_diagnosticsetting.png`).

 Evidence: The KQL query shows successful `GetBlob` operations originating from the internal Private IP (192.168.1.4) (`proj1_remediation_verificiation2_log_output_for_successful_image rendering.png`).
 Conclusion: This audit trail proves that the public internet was bypassed and only the authorized internal "jumpbox" reached the resource.

---

## 💡 Lessons Learned
 Network vs. Identity: Option A (Whitelisting) locks the door but leaves it visible. Option B (Private Link) removes the door from the outside of the building entirely. You must be inside the network to even see the resource.
 Continuous Governance: Security is a cycle. By combining Defender for Cloud for detection, RBAC for identity, and Private Link for networking, we achieve a hardened, enterprise-ready posture.
